cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is focused on studying the feature spaces of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and their ability to achieve viewpoint invariance. This topic is closely related to computer vision and machine learning, which are covered by the cs.CV and cs.LG sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a methodology to quantify the deformation and degeneracy of view manifolds in CNN layers, which involves experimental analysis and could be considered as a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the fine-tuning of pre-trained CNNs, which is a common technique in neural networks and falls under the cs.NE sub-category. Finally, the paper reports interesting results, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
